```

## JavaScript Patterns
- Use modern ES6+ syntax when supported
- Implement proper error handling for all async operations
- Use event delegation for dynamic content
- Maintain clean separation between calendar logic and API calls

## Filtering Implementation
- Implement real-time filtering without page reload
- Use URL parameters to maintain filter state
- Provide clear visual feedback for active filters
- Ensure filters work on mobile devices

## Accessibility Standards
- Use proper ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all features
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios
- Provide alternative text for activity icons

## Performance Optimization
- Minimize DOM manipulation during calendar updates
- Use CSS transforms for animations instead of changing layout properties
- Implement efficient event filtering algorithms
- Lazy load non-critical calendar features

## Browser Compatibility
- Test on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge
- Provide fallbacks for older browsers (IE11+)
- Use progressive enhancement approach
- Validate with real mobile devices